      "message": "nit: Might be less confusing to call this \"Key\" or \"DatastoreKey\" to differentiate from Id.\n\nAlternatively, why not just use the Id from GetNextId as the Key ID?\n\nAlso note that Javascript doesn\u0027t support 64-bit integers. I assume Datastore will assign Ids using the full 64 bits. (We use int64 for some of the fields below, but the timestamp format fits in 52 bits, which JS supports, and RepeatAfterDays is never more than 7.)",
